Policy_Details: All individuals age >=5 must wear a mask while indoors in premises open to the public. Exceptions: 
Maintain at >6ft of separation at all times from anyone outside household; 
Engaged in federal, state, or county govt services at such a service location; 
Seated at a bar/restaurant to eat/drink, or while immediately consuming food/beverages; Engaged in exercise; 
Engaged in an occupation preventing mask-wearing; 
Obtaining a service/good that requires temporary removal of mask; or, 
Has a medical condition, mental health condition, or disability that prevents mask-wearing.    Source information: https://lincoln.ne.gov/city/covid19/pdf/directed-health-measures-2020-09.pdf

